          <h3>1. "You only pay for what you use"</h3>
          <p>No reserved capacity. No idle costs. Pure usage-based billing.</p>
          <p class="reality"><strong>Reality with Lambda:</strong> Cold starts, regional fees, complex pricing. Minimum \$5-20/month for basic APIs.</p>
          <p class="clodo"><strong>Clodo Reality:</strong> True pay-per-use. \$0.30-0.50/month for 10M requests. Zero minimum.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="promise">
          <h3>2. "Infinite scalability"</h3>
          <p>Handle traffic spikes without provisioning. Scale automatically worldwide.</p>
          <p class="reality"><strong>Reality with Lambda:</strong> Scales per region. Requires CloudFront for global. Concurrency limits. Setup complexity.</p>
          <p class="clodo"><strong>Clodo Reality:</strong> Unlimited concurrency. 300+ locations by default. Auto-scaling built-in globally.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="promise">
          <h3>3. "Deploy globally in seconds"</h3>
          <p>One deploy command. Instant global availability. No ops.</p>
          <p class="reality"><strong>Reality with Lambda:</strong> Requires manual multi-region setup. CloudFormation or CDK. Infrastructure code. 10+ minutes.</p>
          <p class="clodo"><strong>Clodo Reality:</strong> One command. 15 seconds. Deployed to 300+ locations automatically.</p>
        </div>
