      <h2>How Clodo Closes the Gap</h2>

      <div class="solutions">
        <div class="solution">
          <h3>‚úÖ True Pay-Per-Use Pricing</h3>
          
          <p><strong>What Clodo does differently:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Fixed CPU cost: \$0.50 per 1M milliseconds (all tiers)</li>
            <li>No cold start penalty</li>
            <li>No regional multipliers</li>
            <li>No minimum monthly fee</li>
            <li>Requests included in free tier</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Real example: 10M requests/month, 50ms avg execution</strong></p>
          <div class="cost-comparison">
            <div class="option lambda">
              <h4>AWS Lambda</h4>
              <p>Requests: 10M √ó \$0.20/M = \$2.00</p>
              <p>Duration: 500M ms √ó \$0.0000166667 = \$8,333</p>
              <p>Database: \$100-300</p>
              <p class="total">Total: ~\$8,435/month</p>
            </div>

            <div class="option clodo">
              <h4>Clodo</h4>
              <p>CPU: 500M ms √ó \$0.50/M = \$250</p>
              <p>D1 Database: ~\$1</p>
              <p>KV Storage: Included</p>
              <p class="total">Total: ~\$251/month</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="savings"><strong>Savings: \$8,184/month (97% cheaper!)</strong></p>
        </div>

        <div class="solution">
          <h3>‚úÖ Zero Cold Starts</h3>
          
          <p><strong>The problem:</strong> Lambda warms up when called. First request = 100-300ms. Traffic spike = many cold starts.</p>

          <p><strong>Clodo solution:</strong> Workers run on V8 isolates that are always warm. No function initialization. Sub-5ms execution time even at 1M requests/second.</p>

          <p><strong>Impact:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Consistent latency: Always 5-50ms, never 100-300ms</li>
            <li>Better UX: No slow first request</li>
            <li>Better business: Higher conversion rates with faster responses</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="solution">
          <h3>‚úÖ True Global Deployment</h3>
          
          <p><strong>The problem:</strong> Lambda is regional. Requires CloudFront. Manual multi-region setup. Users far from region get high latency.</p>

          <p><strong>Clodo solution:</strong> Deploy once. Runs in 300+ Cloudflare locations globally. Your code automatically executes closest to the user.</p>

          <pre><code># One command deploys globally
wrangler deploy

# Your API is now at:
# - Tokyo (5ms latency from Japan)
# - London (5ms latency from UK)
# - Sydney (5ms latency from Australia)
# - S√£o Paulo (5ms latency from Brazil)
# - ... and 296 more locations</code></pre>

          <p><strong>Impact:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>10-50ms latency from anywhere in the world</li>
            <li>No geographic bottlenecks</li>
            <li>Better global user experience</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="solution">
          <h3>‚úÖ Built-in Database</h3>
          
          <p><strong>The problem:</strong> Lambda needs external database (RDS, DynamoDB). Adds cost, complexity, latency.</p>

          <p><strong>Clodo solution:</strong> D1 SQLite included. Distributed globally. Queries run in milliseconds near users.</p>

          <pre><code>// No external database setup needed
const user = await db
  .prepare('SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = ?')
  .bind(userId)
  .first();

// Result: <5ms query time from anywhere in the world</code></pre>

          <p><strong>Impact:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>\$100-300/month database cost eliminated</li>
            <li>Sub-5ms query latency globally</li>
            <li>No connection pooling setup needed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="solution">
          <h3>‚úÖ Minimal Operations</h3>
          
          <p><strong>The problem:</strong> Serverless still requires: CloudWatch setup, IAM policies, auto-scaling config, error monitoring, deployment pipelines.</p>

          <p><strong>Clodo solution:</strong> Automatic monitoring. Logs visible immediately. Simple wrangler.toml config. Built-in analytics.</p>

          <pre><code># View real-time logs
wrangler tail

# That's it. No CloudWatch setup.</code></pre>

          <p><strong>Impact:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>No DevOps expertise required</li>
            <li>Faster debugging and troubleshooting</li>
            <li>Less maintenance burden</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="solution">
          <h3>‚úÖ Performance by Default</h3>
          
          <p><strong>The problem:</strong> Lambda requires optimization knowledge. Cold starts, regions, caching‚Äîall manual.</p>

          <p><strong>Clodo solution:</strong> Edge computing baked in. Automatic caching. Intelligent routing. No config needed.</p>

